## Key Design Decisions and Patterns

### Pattern: Effect → Imperative Bridge

All tool `execute()` handlers, command `handler()` callbacks, and event handlers are **imperative async functions**. Effects are run via `runtime.runPromise(effect)` which converts Effect failures to thrown exceptions. The outer `try-catch` in each handler converts Effect.fail → `{ isError: true }` result.

### Pattern: Service Layer Stack

```
LoggerLayer
├── SoulSpecLoader.Default
│   └── Ref<Map<string, SoulManifest>> (cache)
├── ActiveSoulPersistence.Default
│   └── ActiveSoul persistence at ~/.pi/agent/.active-soul.json
└── NodeFileSystem.layer
    └── @effect/platform FileSystem
```

### Pattern: Error Handling

- `Data.TaggedError` classes for domain errors (SoulNotFoundError, ManifestParseError, FileSystemError)
- `Effect.catchAll` / `Effect.catchTag` for recovery inside Effect.gen
- Outer `try-catch` only at the imperative boundary (tool/command/event handlers)
- Errors from optional file reads are silently swallowed (`.pipe(Effect.catchAll(() => Effect.succeed(undefined)))`)

### Pattern: Cache Strategy

- `Ref<Map<string, SoulManifest>>` for the manifest cache
- Cache populated on `load()` — re-reads for level >= 3 (full disclosure)
- `Ref.update()` for immutable Map mutations

### Pattern: Path Handling

- Tilde expansion (`expandHome()`) is a sync boundary function using `process.env.HOME`
- All paths expanded before passing to `@effect/platform` FileSystem methods
- Path concatenation uses string interpolation (`${base}/${name}/soul.json`)
- No `path.join` — avoid `node:path` import entirely

---

## Forbidden Patterns and Must-Follow Rules

### MUST

- [ ] Use `Effect.Service` for all services — never `Context.Tag` for new code
- [ ] Use `Effect.gen(function* () { ... })` for Effect composition
- [ ] Use `yield*` (never `yield`) inside Effect.gen
- [ ] Use `return yield* Effect.fail(...)` for explicit error termination
- [ ] Use `import type { ... }` for type-only imports
- [ ] Use `const` objects with `type` aliases instead of `enum`
- [ ] Prefer `"` over `'` for strings (match existing code style)
- [ ] Use `as const` for string literal const objects
- [ ] Use `readonly` on all interface/class properties where possible
- [ ] Use `bun add` for all dependency installation

### MUST NOT

- [ ] No `try-catch` inside `Effect.gen` blocks
- [ ] No `as any`, `as never`, `as unknown` type assertions
- [ ] No `yield` (without `*`) inside `Effect.gen`
- [ ] No `enum` keyword
- [ ] No `node:fs`, `node:path`, `node:os` imports
- [ ] No edits to `src/.source/soul.ts` (read-only reference)
- [ ] No `npm install` — must use `bun add`
- [ ] No speculative features or abstractions beyond the reference impl
- [ ] No changes to external API contracts (tool names, param shapes, return shapes, event shapes, persistence file format)

