### Can `SoulSpecLoader` be tested with a mock `FileSystem` via `Layer.succeed`?

**Yes.** `Effect.Service` auto-generates a tag and a `Default` layer. The `Default` layer requires `FileSystem`. A test layer can replace `FileSystem` with a mock:

```typescript
import { FileSystem } from "@effect/platform";
import { Effect, Layer } from "effect";
import { SoulSpecLoader } from "./src/loader";

const mockFileSystem: FileSystem.FileSystem = FileSystem.of({
  exists: (_path: string) => Effect.succeed(true),
  readDirectory: (_path: string) => Effect.succeed(["test-soul"]),
  readFileString: (path: string) => {
    if (path.endsWith("soul.json")) {
      return Effect.succeed(
        JSON.stringify({
          spec_version: "1.0",
          name: "test",
          display_name: "Test Soul",
          version: "1.0.0",
          description: "A test soul",
          author: { name: "test" },
          license: "MIT",
          tags: [],
          category: "test",
          compatibility: { models: [], frameworks: [] },
          allowed_tools: [],
          recommended_skills: [],
          files: { soul: "SOUL.md" },
          deprecated: false,
          environment: "virtual",
          interaction_mode: "text",
          sensors: [],
          actuators: [],
        }),
      );
    }
    if (path.endsWith("SOUL.md")) return Effect.succeed("Hello soul");
    return Effect.fail(new Error("not found"));
  },
  // ... remaining required methods minimally implemented
} as FileSystem.FileSystem);

const testLayer = Layer.provide(
  SoulSpecLoader.Default,
  Layer.succeed(FileSystem.FileSystem, mockFileSystem),
);

const effect = SoulSpecLoader.pipe(
  Effect.flatMap((loader) => loader.load("test-soul", 2)),
  Effect.provide(testLayer),
);
```

**Simplest possible test:** Run the effect above, assert the returned `SoulManifest.display_name === "Test Soul"` and `soul_content === "Hello soul"`.

