| -------------------- | ---- | ------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| `src/loader.ts`      | 17   | `TS2488`: Type 'typeof FileSystem' must have `[Symbol.iterator]()` |
| `src/persistence.ts` | 14   | `TS2488`: Type 'typeof FileSystem' must have `[Symbol.iterator]()` |

### Diagnosis

`@effect/platform`'s `index.d.ts` does:

```typescript
export * as FileSystem from "./FileSystem.js";
```

This creates a **namespace** import. When the code does:

```typescript
import { FileSystem } from "@effect/platform";
const fs = yield * FileSystem;
```

`FileSystem` is the namespace object (module-level exports), not the `Tag<FileSystem, FileSystem>`. A namespace has no `[Symbol.iterator]`.

### Fix

Change **both** imports to the subpath import:

**`src/loader.ts:2`** and **`src/persistence.ts:2`**:

```typescript
// BEFORE
import { FileSystem } from "@effect/platform";

// AFTER
import { FileSystem } from "@effect/platform/FileSystem";
```

**`src/services/soul-fs.ts:1`** — same fix:

```typescript
import { FileSystem } from "@effect/platform/FileSystem";
```

The subpath `@effect/platform/FileSystem` directly exports `const FileSystem: Tag<FileSystem, FileSystem>` (line 346 of its `.d.ts`), which CAN be yielded via `yield*`.

### Verification

The actual Tag definition in `node_modules/@effect/platform/dist/dts/FileSystem.d.ts:346`:

```typescript
export declare const FileSystem: Tag<FileSystem, FileSystem>;
```

