## 2. Audit Findings by Category

### 2a. Effect.Service Pattern — SoulSpecLoader (`loader.ts:1-230`) & ActiveSoulPersistence (`persistence.ts:1-83`)

**✅ Correct usage:** Both services use `Effect.Service<X>()("app/X", { effect: Effect.gen(...), dependencies: [] })`. No missing `Effect.Service` type params.

**✅ Dependencies:** Both declare `const fs = yield* FileSystem` inside `Effect.gen` body. Correct pattern for Effect.Service constructor.

**✅ `.Default` layers:** Auto-generated by Effect.Service. Used in `.pi/extensions/soul.ts:19-23` with `Layer.provideMerge`.

**✅ Layer memoization:** Both compose `NodeFileSystem.layer` via `Layer.provideMerge`. Effect layer system memoizes by identity, so `NodeFileSystem.layer` is evaluated once even though it appears in two `provideMerge` calls.

**Key lines:**

- `loader.ts:6-7` — `Yield* FileSystem` from correct import path (`@effect/platform/FileSystem`)
- `loader.ts:8-9` — `Ref.make<Map<string, SoulManifest>>(new Map())`
- `persistence.ts:8-9` — Same FileSystem pattern

### 2b. Error Boundaries

**✅ NO try-catch inside Effect.gen** — The only `try-catch` block found in the initial review (`persistence.ts:54-62`) has been refactored to `Effect.try` (current code at persistence.ts:51-61):

```typescript
