### Gap 5: camelCase→snake_case JSON Mapping (CRITICAL)

**Status: MISSING — This is the #1 compliance gap**

The reference `src/.source/soul.ts` has a `parseManifest(data, soulDir)` method (lines ~510-650) that maps every camelCase JSON field from `soul.json` to snake_case TS fields:

**Reference `parseManifest` mappings (excerpt):**

```
data.specVersion            → spec_version
data.displayName            → display_name
data.author?.name           → author.name
data.author?.github         → author.github
data.compatibility?.openclaw → compatibility.openclaw
data.compatibility?.minTokenContext → compatibility.min_token_context
data.allowedTools           → allowed_tools
data.recommendedSkills / data.skills → recommended_skills
data.files?.userTemplate    → files.user_template
data.files?.avatar          → files.avatar
data.deprecated             → deprecated
data.supersededBy           → superseded_by
data.repository             → repository
data.environment            → environment
data.interactionMode        → interaction_mode
data.hardwareConstraints    → hardware_constraints
data.safety?.physical?.contactPolicy → safety.physical.contact_policy
data.safety?.physical?.emergencyProtocol → safety.physical.emergency_protocol
data.safety?.physical?.operatingZone → safety.physical.operating_zone
data.safety?.physical?.maxSpeed → safety.physical.max_speed
data.sensors (keyed map)   → sensors[] (array with `name` field)
data.actuators (keyed map) → actuators[] (array with `name` field)
```

**Current new loader.ts behavior:**

`loader.ts:84`:

```ts
const manifest = yield * readJsonFile<SoulManifest>(fs, manifestPath);
```

`readJsonFile<T>` (soul-fs.ts:23-43):

```ts
return fs.readFileString(soulPath).pipe(
  Effect.flatMap((content: string) =>
    Effect.try({
      try: () => JSON.parse(content) as T, // <-- DIRECT CAST, NO FIELD MAPPING
      catch: (cause) => new ManifestParseError({ path: soulPath, cause }),
    }),
  ),
);
```

**This means:** If `soul.json` uses camelCase (as the spec does), all fields are loaded as-is. Since `SoulManifest` expects snake_case, the manifest will have:

- `spec_version` = `undefined` (spec has `specVersion`)
- `display_name` = `undefined` (spec has `displayName`)
- `files.user_template` = `undefined` (spec has `files.userTemplate`)
- etc.

**Additionally missing from the reference `parseManifest`:**

1. Legacy `skills` → `recommendedSkills` backward compatibility (`data.recommendedSkills || data.skills || []`)
2. Sensor keyed-object to array conversion (`Object.entries(data.sensors || {})` → `[{ name, type, ... }]`)
3. Actuator keyed-object to array conversion (same pattern)
4. String skill entries → object format (`typeof skill === "string"` → `{ name: skill, required: false }`)
5. Enum string mapping (`Mobility[data.hardwareConstraints.mobility] || Mobility.STATIONARY`)

**CRITICAL FINDING:** Without `parseManifest`, the implementation cannot read any real `soul.json` file written to spec. Every field using camelCase will silently be `undefined`. This affects at minimum: `spec_version`, `display_name`, `allowed_tools`, `recommended_skills`, `files.user_template`, `superseded_by`, `interaction_mode`, `min_token_context`, `hardware_constraints`, `safety.physical.contact_policy`, `safety.physical.emergency_protocol`, `safety.physical.operating_zone`, `safety.physical.max_speed`, `sensors`, `actuators`.

