## 3. Integration Test Pattern

### Architecture

The project uses `Effect.Service` which auto-generates a `Default` layer requiring `FileSystem`. The test pattern is:

```typescript
import { Effect, Layer } from "effect";
import { FileSystem } from "@effect/platform/FileSystem";
import { SoulSpecLoader } from "./src/loader";
import { ActiveSoulPersistence } from "./src/persistence";

// Use the built-in FileSystem.layerNoop for testing
// This creates a minimal mock that doesn't crash on unused methods
const testFs = FileSystem.makeNoop({
  exists: (path: string) => Effect.succeed(true),
  readDirectory: (path: string) => Effect.succeed(["test-soul"]),
  readFileString: (path: string) => {
    if (path.endsWith("soul.json")) {
      return Effect.succeed(JSON.stringify(MOCK_SOUL_MANIFEST));
    }
    if (path.endsWith("SOUL.md")) return Effect.succeed("# I am a test soul\n\nI help test.");
    if (path.endsWith("IDENTITY.md")) return Effect.succeed("Name: TestBot\nRole: tester");
    return Effect.fail(new Error("ENOENT"));
  },
  writeFileString: (_path: string, _data: string) => Effect.void,
  makeDirectory: (_path: string, _options?: any) => Effect.void,
  remove: (_path: string, _options?: any) => Effect.void,
});

// Provide the mock to the loader
const testLayer = Layer.provide(SoulSpecLoader.Default, Layer.succeed(FileSystem, testFs));

// Test effect
const loadTestSoul = Effect.gen(function* () {
  const loader = yield* SoulSpecLoader;
  return yield* loader.load("test-soul", 2);
});

const result = await Effect.runPromise(Effect.provide(loadTestSoul, testLayer));
```

### Integration test scenarios

| Test                                       | Description                                                        |
| ------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| `SoulSpecLoader.load("test-soul", 2)`      | Happy path: loads manifest + level 2 content                       |
| `SoulSpecLoader.getActiveSouls()`          | Returns non-empty list when dirs have soul.json                    |
| `ActiveSoulPersistence.save("mytest", 2)`  | Writes active-soul.json with correct fields                        |
| `ActiveSoulPersistence.load()`             | Returns `Option.some` with saved data                              |
| `ActiveSoulPersistence.clear()`            | Removes file (no-op in mock)                                       |
| Persistence → load → save → load roundtrip | `save("x", 2)` then `load()` returns `Some({soul: "x", level: 2})` |

